<body>
<h1><a 
href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/User:CitationTool">
David Mertz' Citation Tool for Wikipedia</a></h1>

<p><b>Instructions:</b> <i>Enter the name of the page whose m:Cite.php 
references you wish to analyze</i> (leave field blank to select a random 
article; few random articles utilize m:Cite.php, however).</p>  
<p>Please 
<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=User_talk:CitationTool&action=edit&section=new">
report any bugs here</a>. <i>This software is released to the public domain, 
<a href="http://gnosis.cx/download/wikipedia/">see the source and logs here.
</a></i></p>

<form method="get" action="http://gnosis.cx/cgi-bin/check_refs.py">
<input type="text" name="pageName" size="30" maxlength="256" />
<input type="submit" name="action" value="Analyze" />
<input type="submit" name="action" value="Harvardize" /> 
<input type="submit" name="action" value="Dump" />
</form>


